New Records: Zach Edey became the first rookie in NBA history with at least 20 points and 10 rebounds while hitting at least 90% of his shots.
Key Match Events: Zach Edey finished the game with 25 points, 12 rebounds, four blocks, and one steal.
Edey hit 11-of-12 shots, including 1-for-1 from deep.
Edey had a 3-pointer in the third quarter that stunned the crowd inside the Barclays Center.
Post-Match Reflections: Zach Edey has received a ton of flak for the underwhelming start to his NBA career but finally put together his best game of the season against the Nets.
Some fans are ready to crown Zach Edey as the ROY winner after one great game, but he will have to outplay every rookie from the 2024 draft class to earn the honor.
